## ğŸ¦ Step-by-Step: Small Claims (â‰¤ \$7,500)

### ğŸ”¹ Step 1: Choose County Court

File in the county where:

* The **job was performed**, or
* The **client resides or does business**

ğŸ“Œ Court Finder: [https://www.courts.state.co.us/Courts/County/](https://www.courts.state.co.us/Courts/County/)

---

### ğŸ”¹ Step 2: Prepare Required Forms

Download and fill:

* **JDF 250**: Notice, Claim, and Summons
  [https://www.courts.state.co.us/Forms/PDF/JDF%20250.pdf](https://www.courts.state.co.us/Forms/PDF/JDF%20250.pdf)
* Optional: Statement of Claim (JDF 256) if needed for clarity
* Attach:

  * Invoice/contract
  * Screenshot proof
  * Service photo(s)
  * Total owed breakdown

---

### ğŸ”¹ Step 3: File the Case

Options:

* File in-person at county courthouse
* Or call clerk and request e-filing / mail-in submission (depends on court)

ğŸ’µ Filing Fee:

* \$0.01 â€“ \$500 = \$31
* \$500.01 â€“ \$7,500 = \$55

Paid by cash, check, or card at clerkâ€™s window. Get a **receipt**.

ğŸ“ Save receipt scan under:

```
/lawsuits/client-name/filing/
```

---

### ğŸ”¹ Step 4: Serve the Defendant

Methods (choose one):

* [ ] ğŸ§ Personal service (sheriff or process server â€“ \~\$35â€“\$60)
* [ ] ğŸ“¬ Certified mail (if allowed by clerk)

ğŸ” Must serve AT LEAST 15 days before court date

ğŸ“ Save:

* Proof of service
* Process server invoice
* Certified mail receipt & tracking #

Store under:

```
/lawsuits/client-name/service/
```

---

### ğŸ”¹ Step 5: Prepare for Hearing

* Rehearse your **statement of claim** (1â€“2 minutes)
* Bring:

  * Original contract or quote
  * Photos (before/after)
  * Messages/emails
  * Invoice or transaction logs
* Make **3 copies** of all docs (you, judge, defendant)

Use this repo to print:

```
/lawsuits/client-name/
ğŸ”¼ memo.md
ğŸ”¼ contract.md
ğŸ”¼ payment-summary.md
ğŸ”¼ photos/
ğŸ”¼ screenshots/
ğŸ”¼ court-filing/
